parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front control arm can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit a loud clunking or banging noise
and the vehicle may pull to one side or vibrate excessively. In some cases
causing the vehicle to lose control or become difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the rear suspension cross member can cause the control arm to break, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit a loud clunking or banging noise
the rear of the vehicle may sag or vibrate excessively
and the control arm may break
causing the vehicle to lose control or become difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death to occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
or fail to deploy in a crash.
